<div class="email-policy-text">Please check your documents when you receive them and notify us of any discrepancies. Cancellation / interruption insurance is available and highly recommended. <b>NOTE, ONCE TRAVEL INSURANCE IS PURCHASED IT IS NON-REFUNDABLE</b>. It is the passenger’s responsibility to have appropriate documents for identification. It is the passenger’s responsibility to be aware of any cancellation penalties. It is the passenger’s responsibility to be informed of any state department warnings where they are traveling. It is the passenger's responsibility to confirm their ability to enter the country they are traveling to, including but not limited to, confirming passport validity meets the requirements for entry as well as any visa requirements or prohibitions for entering certain countries due to prior convictions or otherwise. They also need to be aware of any health risks and take the appropriate precautions. All monies paid for travel is subject to the refund policy outlined below.</div>
<div class="email-policy-text">Suppliers is defined as the wholesaler, hotel, airline, tour operator, transportation provider, or any other supplier of travel.</div>
<div class="email-policy-text"><b>Refunds</b>, If due from suppliers will be made to our customers only after the monies have been received from these sources by us. This process may take a minimum of 5-7 business days and possibly longer.</div>
<div class="email-policy-text"><b>Barefoot Bridal Cancellation Policy</b> Your reservation is part of a Flexible Group, a group of individual reservations that have been linked together therefore, cancellations and night reductions must be received in writing at least 1 business day prior to {{ $group->cancellation_date->format('F d, Y') }}, to be refundable. Any changes in bookings that are reductions after this deadline will be considered a cancellation and will be completely nonrefundable. Any changes made to your reservation after the initial booking is subject to new rates and availability. If a cancellation request is not made in time, it will be nonrefundable, unless the supplier waives their cancellation penalty, in which case your booking will be subject to the following refund policy: Any booking canceled by the client before the trip begins will incur a $250 per person non-refundable cancellation fee in addition to any fees charged by the supplier. If the trip or any component thereof is canceled to no fault of the client (eg, acts of God), the client agrees that Barefoot Bridal has no liability and that all refunds of monies paid shall never exceed a refund of monies paid to and/or via Barefoot Bridal, less the cost of services assessed at $250 per booking.</div>
<div class="email-policy-text"><b>Barefoot Bridal Chargeback Policy</b> Notwithstanding anything that says otherwise in your cardholder agreement, you agree not to submit any chargebacks for your reservation If a chargeback is received prior to a reservation's cancellation date, your reservation will be cancelled immediately. If a chargeback is received once the reservation has become non-refundable, your reservation will be cancelled immediately and the group leader will be responsible for the total cost of your reservation.</div>
<div class="email-policy-text"><b>Price Changes By The Travel Supplier</b> Once payment has been applied to a booking and up until the time of departure, Barefoot Bridal and its agents are neither responsible for nor obliged to honor any discounts, specials or promotions offered by suppliers of travel products. We are not responsible for checking to see if any prices have been reduced. Disclosure Notice Barefoot Bridal (hereinafter "TRAVEL AGENT") is acting as a mere agent for suppliers in selling travel-related services, or in accepting reservations or bookings for services that are not directly supplied by this Travel Agency (such as air and ground transportation, hotel accommodations, meals, tours, cruises, etc.) Travel Agency, therefore, shall not be responsible for breach of contract, failure to comply with any laws such as the Americans and Disabilities Act, or any intentional or negligent actions or omissions on the part of such suppliers, which result in any loss, damage, delay, inconvenience, or injury to travelers or traveler’s companions or group members. Unless the term "guaranteed" is specifically stated in writing on your tickets, invoices, or reservation itinerary, Travel Agency does not guarantee any of such suppliers’ rates, bookings, reservations, connections, scheduling, or handling of baggage or other personal effects. Travel Agent shall not be responsible for any injuries, damages, or losses caused to any traveler in connection with terrorist activities, social or labor unrest, mechanical or construction failures, or difficulties, diseases, local laws, climatic conditions, abnormal conditions or developments, or any other actions, omissions, or conditions outside the travel agent’s control.</div>
<div class="email-policy-text">Traveler assumes complete and full responsibility for and hereby releases the agent from any duty of checking and verifying any and all passport, visa, vaccinations, or other entry requirements of each destination, and all safety and security conditions of such destinations, during the length of the proposed travel. By embarking upon his/her travel, the traveler voluntarily assumes all risks involved in such travel, whether expected or unexpected. Traveler’s retention of tickets, reservations, or bookings after issuance shall constitute a consent to the above and an agreement on his/her part to convey the contents hereto to his/her travel companions or group members. I understand that the airline tickets or air tours I am purchasing are subject to supplemental price increases that may be imposed after the date of purchase. Post-purchase price increases may be applied due to additional costs imposed by a supplier or government. I acknowledge that I may be charged additional sums by Barefoot Bridal to offset increased fees, fuel surcharges, taxes, fluctuations in foreign exchange markets or any combination thereof. I hereby consent to any post-purchase price increases and authorize Barefoot Bridal to charge my credit card for such additional amounts.</div>
